<task id="074" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>P23.L5 — LOW-tier closeout + archive-ledger reconciliation</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <completed-date>2026-05-31</completed-date>
    <completion-notes>
      Fresh full-suite TRX measurements captured for both projects.
      Unit: 6030 total / 5893 pass / 4 fail / 133 skip (−338 / −98.8% vs Phase 0; −168 / −97.7% vs Phase 1 end).
      Integration: 422 total / 323 pass / 47 fail / 52 skip (−151 / −76.3% vs Phase 0; matches post-027 exactly).
      Wave 2.5 cumulative archive count = 0 across tasks 070/071/072/073 (NFR-04 trivially satisfied).
      Real-bug ledger schema-validated (12 entries; severity + fix-by + owner-TBD complete on all).
      Authoritative baseline written: `baseline/post-phase23-authoritative-2026-05-31.md`.
      Archive ledger created with zero-archives canonical entry: `ledgers/archive-ledger.md`.
      Phase 2+3 exit gate declared **PARTIAL CLOSURE**: 51 residual failures (4 unit + 47 integration)
      remain and CANNOT remain `Failed` at project close per §4.3 / NFR-10 — DEFERRED to Phase 4 task 084
      for re-classification to §6.2 final end-states (`real-bug-pending-fix` / `flaky-quarantined` / `repaired`).
      Insights Layer2 (3) HOLD on sibling sign-off; AnalysisContextBuilder (1) new emergent — both to Phase 4.
      Integration residuals (37 param-infer + 9 Upload + 1 PrecedentAdmin) carry forward unchanged from post-027.
      No production code changes (NFR-01 verified clean working tree).
    </completion-notes>
    <estimated-effort>1-2 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-2-3, low-tier, p23-l, bff-api, testing, verification-gate, closeout</tags>
    <parallel-group>23-L-gate</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Verification gate for tasks 070, 071, 072, 073; must run AFTER all 4 batches complete to reconcile cumulative archive count and document tier completion</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>STANDARD</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Verify the LOW-tier P23.L track is fully closed out by reconciling the work of tasks
    070, 071, 072, and 073. This task is a gate: it runs ONLY after all 4 batches complete and
    validates the tier-level zero-failure state per FR-19.

    Steps:
    1. Confirm tasks 070, 071, 072, 073 are all status=completed in TASK-INDEX.md
    2. Run LOW-tier filter: zero failures across all triaged files
    3. Tally cumulative archive count across all 4 batches
    4. If cumulative archive count exceeds owner's pre-approved batch ceiling (per NFR-04
       per-batch enforcement already done in 070-073), reconcile cumulative totals against
       any owner escalations filed during execution
    5. Reconcile `ledgers/archive-ledger.md` — verify every archived file has a complete entry
       (file path, justification, date)
    6. Document tier completion in `ledgers/repair-ledger.md` with tier metrics

    Per project CLAUDE.md NFR-02: this task does NOT modify test files; it verifies and records.
    If failures remain in the LOW-tier, file an escalation per §4.8 documenting which tests
    remain Failed — do NOT mark the tier closed until zero failures.

    Per §6.2, EVERY test in the LOW-tier must end in `repaired`, `real-bug-pending-fix`,
    `flaky-quarantined`, OR be archived via `*.cs.archived-2026-MM-DD` rename. `Failed` is
    FORBIDDEN at close.
  </prompt>

  <role>Senior test orchestrator running tier-level verification + ledger reconciliation.</role>

  <goal>
    LOW-tier is verified zero-failure across the union of tasks 070-073. `archive-ledger.md` is
    fully reconciled with all entries present + justified. `repair-ledger.md` records tier completion
    as canonical artifact for Phase 4 exit-ledger reconciliation (FR-27).
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="spec">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="archive-ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/archive-ledger.md</file>
    <file purpose="repair-ledger">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md</file>
    <file purpose="batch-1-output">(task 070 output: Api/* batch 1 triaged)</file>
    <file purpose="batch-2-output">(task 071 output: Api/* batch 2 triaged)</file>
    <file purpose="batch-3-output">(task 072 output: Api/* batch 3 triaged)</file>
    <file purpose="batch-4-output">(task 073 output: top-level *EndpointTests triaged)</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="FR-19">All LOW-tier tests must end in §6.2 final end-state (zero failures)</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No production code changes</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-02">No file edits beyond ledger reconciliation; verification-only</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-04">Per-batch &gt;10 archives ceiling already enforced in 070-073; this task documents cumulative count</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.3">No test left in `Failed` state at tier close</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      LOW-tier (~88 files) is the largest tier by file count and has the highest archive ratio.
      Per NFR-04, &gt;10 archives per batch trigger escalation — that was enforced per-batch in
      tasks 070-073. This task reconciles cumulative archive counts across all 4 batches against
      any owner escalations filed during execution, and documents tier-level completion in
      `repair-ledger.md`.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="070" status="not-started">LOW-tier Api/* batch 1</dependency>
      <dependency task="071" status="not-started">LOW-tier Api/* batch 2</dependency>
      <dependency task="072" status="not-started">LOW-tier Api/* batch 3</dependency>
      <dependency task="073" status="not-started">LOW-tier top-level endpoint tests</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/archive-ledger.md</file>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Confirm tasks 070, 071, 072, 073 are status=completed in `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`. If any incomplete, HALT and report.</step>
    <step order="2">Run LOW-tier filter: `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Api|FullyQualifiedName~EndpointTests" -c Release`. Capture TRX output. Verify zero failures.</step>
    <step order="3">If non-zero failures remain, identify each and file escalation per §4.8 OR document as `real-bug-pending-fix` / `flaky-quarantined`. Do NOT mark tier closed if any remain Failed.</step>
    <step order="4">Tally cumulative archive count across batches 070-073. Cross-reference with per-batch escalations (`escalations/archive-approval-T-07{0,1,2,3}.md`) — confirm all owner approvals are recorded.</step>
    <step order="5">Verify `ledgers/archive-ledger.md` has one entry per archived file with: file path, justification (synthetic-smoke equivalence cited), date.</step>
    <step order="6">Append tier section to `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md`: tier name (LOW-tier), date, task IDs (070-073), metrics (files triaged, files repaired, files archived, tests now Passing).</step>
    <step order="7">Mark P23.L complete in `current-task.md`. Verify `git status` shows only ledger updates — no production code changes.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="dotnet">test (LOW-tier filter verification)</tool>
    <tool name="git">status</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/repair-ledger.md (LOW-tier section appended)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/ledgers/archive-ledger.md (reconciled and complete)</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/current-task.md (P23.L marked complete)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet test --filter "FullyQualifiedName~Api|FullyQualifiedName~EndpointTests"` returns zero failures</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ledgers/repair-ledger.md` contains a dated section for LOW-tier with tier metrics</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`ledgers/archive-ledger.md` has one complete entry per archived file (path, justification, date)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All per-batch &gt;10-archive escalations (if any) have owner approval recorded</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No LOW-tier test is in `Failed` state</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`git status` shows only ledger + current-task.md modifications; no production code changes</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
